59 subsection: -
60 (k) Benefits shall not be paid to any individual for any week commencing during an
61 established and customary vacation period or holiday recess if such individual is employed with
62 the employer in the period immediately before such vacation period or holiday recess, and there
63 is a reasonable assurance that such individual will perform such services in the period
64 immediately following such vacation period or holiday recess.
